theories/ConvexChainSplit.v

# Convex-chain monotonicity campaign, rung 3.5: a GENERAL construction of the
# bimonotone split from a purely combinatorial y-unimodality hypothesis on the
# vertex list (convexity not used).  Replaces the per-family hand-built split:
# the split obligation becomes an arithmetic cbn/lra check.  Re-derives the
# diamond split in one line; scales to a convex hexagon (n = 6).
theories/MonotoneChainConstruction.v

# Convex-chain monotonicity campaign, rung 4: the edge-halfplane algebraic
# bridge for interior_hits_one_chain.  Key identity: hp_slack(edge_inward_hp e)q
# equals the signed cross-product used by edge_cross_sign, yielding
# edge_crosses_ray ↔ straddles ∧ hp_slack>0 (inc) / <0 (dec).  Combined with
# height-band chain coverage (chain_increasing_straddles_y), closes
# interior_hits_one_chain for any y-unimodal convex ring whose edge inward
# half-planes are supplied.  Validated on diamond and hexagon.
theories/MonotoneChainCoverage.v
# The y-modulator (first step): half-plane convexity is the all-CCW-left-turns
# orientation form (convex_left_turns); the y-unimodal decomposition predicate and
# its wiring to bimonotone_split; max/min-height vertex infra; diamond + hexagon
# witnesses.  Isolates the remaining "convex => y-unimodal" geometric residual.
theories/ConvexYUnimodal.v
# The y-modulator (crossing bound): from a bimonotone_split, each monotone chain
# is crossed at most once, so a convex / y-unimodal ring is crossed at most twice
# (convex_ray_crosses_le_two) and inside iff crossed exactly once
# (convex_in_ring_iff_one_crossing).  The capstone
# convex_canonical_start_in_ring_iff_one_crossing composes the §11.5k
# no-interior-y-min reduction with the bound: the general convex ring's exact
# one-crossing characterization, conditional on the named residual
# convex_no_interior_ymin.  Three-axiom.  No Admitted.
theories/ConvexRayCrossing.v
# The hot pixel as a convex ring: presents the half-open axis-aligned square
# (HotPixel.in_hot_pixel) as a Ring and connects it to the crossing-number
# point_in_ring.  The two horizontal edges never cross a rightward ray, so the
# pixel is crossed at most twice (pixel_ray_crosses_le_two) and inside iff
# crossed exactly once (pixel_point_in_ring_iff_box) -- a half-open-x / open-y
# box.  Bridge: point_in_ring is a subset of the half-open pixel (total), the
# converse holds off the bottom edge, and a grazing witness on the included
# bottom edge is in_hot_pixel yet not point_in_ring.  Three-axiom.  No Admitted.
theories/HotPixelConvexRing.v

# Bridge: sqrt(3)/2 scaling on the x-axis turns hex-lattice Q-preimages into
# R-geometry (exact equilateral metrics) while making the horizontal-ray
# crossing predicate (`edge_crosses_ray` / ray parity) identical to the
# rational model.  xscale / xscale_edge; the forward bridge xscale_cross_bridge;
# the reverse edge_crosses_ray_xscale_rev (via xscale_inv); the mutual-induction
# parity transport ray_parity_xscale_both / ray_parity_odd_xscale; and the
# ring_edges/map commutation ring_edges_map_xscale.  Supports lifting Q-grid
# regression anchors (Spectre/hat) to the true metric.  Three-axiom.  No Admitted.
theories/HexXScaleBridge.v

# A point-in-ring regression anchor on the SPECTRE aperiodic monotile -- a
