# bevel emitter), the stage-3 handoff bevel_emit_ring_closed, and the
# smooth-case coherence.  MITER emission (via BufferMiter.miter_apex)
# remains the one open join flavour.  No Admitteds.
theories/CurveBevelJoin.v

# Issue #65 curve-aware buffer, rung 13: the MITER assembly -- the last
# open join flavour of the 2b row, emitted as two chords through
# BufferMiter.miter_apex (the JTS#180 Cramer's-rule offset-line
# intersection), with rung 12's bevel as the fallback at joins
# involving arcs (JTS miters only line corners).  Connectors are
# chords with definitional splices, so curve_ring_offset_miter_valid
# keeps the bevel assembly's lean hypothesis set; the geometric tie-in
# miter_connector_apex_sound attaches the perpendicular-distance-d
# property to the emitted apex.  Plus all-chord preservation (the pure
# linear miter emitter), the stage-3 handoff, smooth coherence, and
# generic hd/last/app chain-gluing bricks.  The 2b join EMISSION story
# (round / bevel / miter) is now complete.  No Admitteds.
theories/CurveMiterJoin.v
# Issue #65 curve-aware buffer, rung 14a: the REVERSAL layer for the
# open-chain cap walk (14b) and the SQL/MM ring-orientation flip.
# rev_arc / rev_segment / curve_ring_reverse; circumcircle invariance
# under reversal (rev_arc_center via circumcenter uniqueness, its 4th
# consumer; rev_arc_radius, rev_arc_valid); the ORIENTATION WART made
# formal: arc radial normals are traversal-agnostic but chord
# unit_perp normals FLIP, so offset/reverse commute at OPPOSITE signs
# per kind (offset_rev_chord at -d, offset_rev_arc at +d) -- why JTS
# tracks an explicit side flag.  Headline valid_curve_ring_reverse:
# ring reversal preserves compound-ring validity.  No Admitteds.
theories/CurveReverse.v

# Issue #65 curve-aware buffer, rung 14b: the OPEN-CHAIN two-sided cap
# walk -- the last structural emission gap.  chain_walk (open: offsets
# + chord connectors, no closing join); rung-7 semicircle caps at both
# ends (cap_far via semicircle_cap_connects, cap_start the mirror);
# the right boundary is curve_ring_reverse (chain_walk (-d) c), so the
# 14a reversal lemmas supply all its structure and no per-kind sign
# threading is needed (the orientation-wart-dictated design).
# Headline curve_chain_buffer_valid: a nonempty adjacent chain with
# valid arcs, nondegenerate chords, two-sided safety and d <> 0
# assembles into a CLOSED valid compound ring -- the buffer boundary
# of an open compound line.  Every stage-2 emission (rings AND chains)
# now produces a valid compound ring.  No Admitteds.
theories/CurveCapWalk.v

# Issue #65 / JTS #1195 §7 (BUF-1 / BUF-NEG): the buffer-region AREA companion of
# the BUFFER_REGION oracle (assemble offset boundary + signed area).  Per-arc
# buffer segment area buffer_arc_area = segment_area (r+d); d=0 identity;
# buffer_arc_area_grows (outward buffer grows each arc's segment area); reuse of
# offset_safe_iff_sq (rational EMPTY decision), curve_ring_offset_arcs_valid
# (boundary validity), arc_offset_dist_exact (the parallel-distance property).
# 4-axiom [exact] (segment_area magnitude pulls the sin_lt_x lineage).  The
# geometric "signed area = true Minkowski buffer area" is the deferred P2 frontier,
# pinned by oracle/gen_buffer_region_tests.py.
theories/CurveBufferArea.v

